  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Conceptual Design of the COMPASS Upgrade Tokamak</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-03-06</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">• Design and main systems of the COMPASS Upgrade tokamak are presented. • Medium-sized tokamak, with 5 T toroidal magnetic field, high plasma density, 1 mm mid-plane, power flux, scrape-off decay length (close to ITER) and PB/qAR ratio 70% of ITER. • Closed divertor configuration that allows snowflake divertor configuration. • Ohmic losses reduced via cryogenic cooling of Cu coils down to liquid nitrogen temperatures. • Vacuum vessel possible to heat up to 300 °C. • Two different auxiliary plasma heating systems. 4 MW NBI with variable injection geometry, 4 MW ECRH using ITER-like gyrotrons. • First plasma expected in 2022.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
  </datafield>
